 :tx/rationale "Create task: RFL-1: Register schema attributes for action-outcome tracking — :action/recommended-command, :action/recommended-entity, :action/recommended-impact, :action/outcome, :action/next-command, :action/latency-ms (INV-GUIDANCE-010, INV-SCHEMA-001). BACKGROUND: To learn from agent behavior, we need to RECORD what was recommended and what happened. Each ACP projection becomes an :action/* entity in the store. The outcome (followed/adjacent/ignored) is computed when the agent's next command arrives. This creates a growing dataset of (recommendation, outcome) pairs that feeds the weight learning algorithm. The schema must be in Layer 4 (coordination) since it tracks agent workflow, not project knowledge. APPROACH: (1) Add 6 attributes to layer_4_attributes() in schema.rs: :action/recommended-command (String), :action/recommended-entity (Ref — the task entity), :action/recommended-impact (Double — the R(t) impact score), :action/outcome (Keyword — :action.outcome/followed, /adjacent, /ignored), :action/next-command (String — what the agent actually did), :action/latency-ms (Long — time between recommendation and next command). (2) Define ActionOutcome enum: Followed, Adjacent, Ignored. Tests: (A) braid schema lists all :action/* attributes. (B) ActionOutcome maps to/from keywords correctly. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/schema.rs + crates/braid-kernel/src/guidance.rs"
